2star  aHow did the UK Coalition Government’s policies differ from previous Conservative (or Labour) Government policies? How did the Liberal Democrats influence them? And what can this tell us about the likely policy direction of the Conservative government elected in May 2015? Responding to the political and social policy changes made between 2010-15 this book considers the relationship between the two coalition parties to provide a critical assessment of how their policies affected the British welfare state, including the impact of ‘austerity’. Looking beyond 2015, the contributors consider what the implications of these changes may be for social policy, both the challenges and opportunities, which will present themselves in the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aBaggott, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBailey, Patrick L.J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBall, Stephen J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirrell, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBochel, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBochel, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBochel, Hugh, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChurchill, Harriet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaguerre, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDefty, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Rosalind, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEllison, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators